BACKGROUND: The objective of this article is to describe the design of a study 
to evaluate the clinical and economic effects of a Disease Management model on 
functional health, quality of care and quality of life of persons living in 
homes for the elderly.
METHODS: This study concerns a cluster randomized controlled clinical trial 
among five intervention homes and five usual care homes in the North-West of the 
Netherlands with a total of over 500 residents. All persons who are not 
terminally ill, are able to be interviewed and sign informed consent are 
included. For cognitively impaired persons family proxies will be approached to 
provide outcome information. The Disease Management Model consists of several 
elements: (1) Trained staff carries out a multidimensional assessment of the 
patients functional health and care needs with the interRAI Long Term Care 
Facilities instrument (LTCF). Computerization of the LTCF produces immediate 
identification of problem areas and thereby guides individualized care planning. 
