strategy of FISH testing for all patients, with trastuzumab and chemotherapy for 
FISH positive patients, we estimated the cost per QALY gained to about 561,000 
SEK. The remaining testing and treatment strategies were dominated. Results were 
sensitive to changes in utilities, the risk of breast cancer related death, and 
test characteristics.
CONCLUSION: Our analysis indicate that FISH testing for all patients with 
trastuzumab and chemotherapy treatment for FISH positive patients is a 
cost-effective treatment option from a societal perspective.

